menu_squads
[TITLE]The Manual: Command Squads[/TITLE]
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]How to Get Here[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_SQUADS] from the main view and move close to a squad you'd like to command.
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Description[C:7:0:0]
[B]
You control your army by moving squads around.  These squads are constructed in the military screen.
[B]
[LINK:data/help/menu_military]Military Screen[/LINK]
[B]
There are two ways to control squads:  Stationing and patrol routes.  You can also zoom to the commander of a squad,
lock on a single squad while still moving the cursor, change the cursor speed, and lock on to another squad without have to go find it.
[B]
Station a squad if you just want them to sit someplace until opposition arrives.
[B]
Set them on a patrol route if you want them to cover some ground.
[B]
Soldiers will not follow your orders if they are standing down, eating, drinking, sleeping or heavily-injured.
